<html>
    <head>
<!--include head.txt -->
        <title>
            NYC Department of Records Newsletter Manager
        </title>
    </head>

    <body>
<!--include logo.txt -->
<!--include menu.txt -->
        <h1>
            NYC Department of Records Newsletter Manager
        </h1>

        <ul>
            <li>
                Project requirements
            </li>

            <li>
                Comparison of existing open source products.
                <ol class="nested">
                    <li>
                        <h4>
                            Colossus
                        </h4>

                        <ul class="nested">
                            Pros
                            <li>
                                Provide contact list management features (manage multiple contact lists)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Allow design of emails in application (WYSYWIG Editor)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Allow upload of HTML template in application
                                (Copy &amp; Paste)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Store newsletter statistics (delivery success / failures)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Permissions for sending, managing contact list, and 
                                editing / creating newsletters - Currently Admin Account
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <ul>
                            Cons
                            <li>
                                Allow emails to be sent out - System has this feature but I haven't successfully sent.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                No ability to provide attachments (custom or single attachment)
                            </li>

                             <li>
                                Login with NYC.ID
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <h4>
                            Listmonk
                        </h4>

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <a href="https://github.com/knadh/listmonk"> Github Repository </a>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <ul>
                            Pros
                            <li>
                                Allow emails to be sent out -- I don't know how to test it, but it works on editor's demo.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Allow design of emails in application (WYSYWIG Editor)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Allow upload of HTML template in application
                                (Copy &amp; Paste)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Ability to provide attachments (only pictures support here -
                                there is an attachment button but it doesn't work)
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Store newsletter statistics (delivery success / failures)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Permissions for sending, managing contact list, and
                                editing / creating newsletters - Only Admin Account
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <ul>
                            Cons
                             <li>
                                Login with NYC.ID
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <h4>
                            Mail For Good
                        </h4>

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <a href="https://github.com/freeCodeCamp/mail-for-good"> Github Repository </a>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <ul>
                            Pros
                            <li>
                                Provide contact list management features (manage multiple contact lists)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Allow design of emails in application (WYSYWIG Editor)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Allow upload of HTML template in application
                                (Copy &amp; Paste)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Allow emails to be sent out - System has this feature but I haven't successfully sent.
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Ability to provide attachments (custom or single attachment)
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Store newsletter statistics (delivery success / failures)
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Permissions for sending, managing contact list,
                                and editing / creating newsletters - Currently Admin Account
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <ul>
                            Cons
                             <li>
                                Login with NYC.ID
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                Based on Amazon SES, so account is limited by Amazon.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
        </ul>

    </body>
</html>
